# Contributing to {{projectName}}

{{> header}}

Thank you for considering contributing to **{{projectName}}**! We welcome contributions of all kinds.

## Getting Started

1. Fork the repository.
2. Clone your fork:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/your-username/{{projectName}}.git
   ```
3. Install dependencies:
   ```bash
   {{#eq packageManager "npm"}}npm install{{else}}{{packageManager}} install{{/eq}}
   ```
4. Create a feature branch:
   ```bash
   git checkout -b feat/my-feature
   ```

## Code Style

- Follow the existing conventions in the codebase.
- Run the linter before submitting:
  ```bash
  {{#eq packageManager "npm"}}npm run lint{{else}}{{packageManager}} run lint{{/eq}}
  ```
{{#ne testingFramework "None"}}
- Ensure all tests pass:
  ```bash
  {{#eq packageManager "npm"}}npm test{{else}}{{packageManager}} test{{/eq}}
  ```
{{/ne}}

## Commit Conventions

We follow [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/):

- `feat:` — a new feature
- `fix:` — a bug fix
- `docs:` — documentation changes
- `refactor:` — code refactoring
- `test:` — adding or updating tests
- `chore:` — maintenance tasks

## Pull Request Process

1. Update the `CHANGELOG.md` with details of your changes.
2. Ensure all CI checks pass.
3. Request review from a maintainer.

